/* Abstinence in religion */  Mention of pork in Judaism and Islam is not a form of abstinence; consuming pork is simply forbidden. Pork is forbidden in the same manner as the flesh of carnivores. Among Muslims, at least, the pig is considered an unclean, repulsive animal that is unhealthy to consume -likely a biproduct/cultural explanation of its prohibition. In short, in no is pork considered as a form of 'pleasure' to deny oneself as an act of 'self-discipline' or sacrifice.

There was no concept of India as a nation state circa 1857. Hence there could not be a Indian War of Independence.Moreover, it was a revolt at best with different sections of  Hindustani society fighting to preserve their own narrow self-interests and to protect their respective faiths from religiously invasive activities of British and other Europeans. In other words, it was a revolt against government of the day motivated by religious sentiments and not a War of Independence.
